00:06.506 --> 00:08.342 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And I'm Judy
Woodruff.

00:08.375 --> 00:11.678 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: On the "NewsHour"
tonight: Protests
erupt in Charlotte, North
Carolina,as the

00:11.712 --> 00:15.382 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
city attempts to get to the
bottom of how
a black man was killed by
police.

00:15.415 --> 00:19.653 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Also ahead this
Wednesday,
we sit down with Libertarian
presidential

00:19.686 --> 00:25.525 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
candidate Gary Johnson on what
it means to
his campaign to be left off the
first debate

00:25.559 --> 00:27.294 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
stage.

00:27.327 --> 00:30.831 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Plus, a deep dive
into Donald
Trump's overseas businesses, and
how those

00:30.864 --> 00:33.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
entanglements could affect his
foreign policy.

00:33.267 --> 00:39.106 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And a look at the
historical
gems inside the new National
Museum of African

00:39.139 --> 00:42.876 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
American History and Culture
sitting in the
country's front yard.

00:42.910 --> 00:45.512 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LONNIE Bunch, Director, National
Museum of
African American History and
Culture: I hope

00:45.545 --> 00:51.385 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
this museum will continue to
evolve, continue
to change, because it really has
to be a place

00:51.418 --> 00:56.623 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that is the great convener, that
can bring
anybody and everybody into a
conversation

00:56.657 --> 00:57.891 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
around race.

00:57.925 --> 01:04.364 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All that and more
on tonight's
"PBS NewsHour."

01:04.398 --> 01:06.733 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:06.767 --> 01:17.678 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: It's an all-too-
familiar story,
in a new setting.

01:17.711 --> 01:22.616 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This time, the city of Charlotte
is on edge,
awaiting a second night of
protests over the

01:22.649 --> 01:24.718 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
police killing of a black man.

01:24.751 --> 01:29.489 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The drama began with a Tuesday
confrontation
that sparked a night of trouble.

01:29.523 --> 01:31.425 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
William Brangham begins our
coverage.

01:31.458 --> 01:37.097 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Within hours
of the fatal
shooting, protests boiled over
in North Carolina's

01:37.130 --> 01:38.098 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
largest city.

01:38.131 --> 01:41.368 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The victim was 43-year-old Keith
Lamont Scott.

01:41.401 --> 01:44.404 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And his sister, who didn't give
her name,
said he was unarmed.

01:44.438 --> 01:48.709 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOMAN: They said, hands up, he
got a gun,
he got a gun.

01:48.742 --> 01:50.010 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Pow, pow, pow, pow.

01:50.043 --> 01:51.011 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
That's it.

01:51.044 --> 01:52.679 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
He had no gun.

01:52.713 --> 01:55.582 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Another woman,
claiming
to be Scott's daughter, went on
Facebook,

01:55.615 --> 02:00.621 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
saying he'd had a book, not a
gun, and also
had an unspecified disability.

02:00.654 --> 02:05.959 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In short order, a crowd blocked
traffic on
Interstate 85, throwing rocks,
and destroying

02:05.993 --> 02:07.127 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
police cars.

02:07.160 --> 02:10.697 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Some looted a tractor-trailer
and set it on
fire.

02:10.731 --> 02:13.066 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Others broke into a nearby
Wal-Mart.

02:13.100 --> 02:17.738 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Police eventually used tear gas
to quell the
violence, but 16 officers were
injured.

02:17.771 --> 02:21.708 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This morning, police chief Kerr
Putney urged
people to step back and be calm.

02:21.742 --> 02:23.643 align:left position:25%,start line:73.33% size:75%
KERR PUTNEY,
Charlotte-Mecklenburg, North
Carolina, Police Chief: It's
time to change

02:23.677 --> 02:30.984 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the narrative, because I can
tell you from
the facts that the story is a
little bit different

02:31.018 --> 02:34.388 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
as to how it's been portrayed so
far, especially
through social media.

02:34.421 --> 02:38.592 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: As Putney told
it, officers
had been at an apartment
complex, searching

02:38.625 --> 02:41.661 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
for a suspect, when they saw
Scott get out
of a car.

02:41.695 --> 02:44.831 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They say he did have a gun, and
refused to
put it down.

02:44.865 --> 02:52.406 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KERR PUTNEY: In spite of the
verbal commands,
Mr. Scott, as I said, exited his
vehicle armed

02:52.439 --> 02:58.912 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
with a handgun, as the officers
continued
to yell at him to drop it.

02:58.945 --> 03:06.086 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He stepped out, posing a threat
to the officers,
and officer Brentley Vinson
subsequently fired

03:06.119 --> 03:08.055 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
his weapon, striking the
subject.

03:08.088 --> 03:12.125 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: The officer,
who is also
black, was placed on
administrative leave,

03:12.159 --> 03:14.494 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
which is standard procedure in
such cases.

03:14.528 --> 03:18.698 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Meanwhile, local activists and
ministers called
for an economic boycott of
Charlotte.

03:18.732 --> 03:23.970 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN BARNETT, Civil Rights
Attorney: Across
the country, we are being shot
down, shot

03:24.004 --> 03:24.971 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
down.

03:25.005 --> 03:26.540 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Very few cops go to jail for
that.

03:26.573 --> 03:30.077 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: And by late
this afternoon,
protests were starting up again.

03:30.110 --> 03:34.981 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This incident came just a day
after graphic
video from Tulsa, Oklahoma, that
showed an

03:35.015 --> 03:37.317 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
officer shooting an unarmed
black man.

03:37.350 --> 03:39.719 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm
William Brangham.

03:39.753 --> 03:44.024 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: We will hear from
the mayor of
Charlotte after the news
summary.

03:44.057 --> 03:48.428 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: In the day's
other news: The
Federal Reserve held fast on
keeping a key

03:48.462 --> 03:51.965 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
short-term interest rate near
record lows.

03:51.998 --> 03:57.404 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
