to run Than
might have been previously
thought.

04:15.088 --> 04:16.923 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
That's good news.

04:16.957 --> 04:21.328 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Yellen did
suggest an interest
rate increase is likely before
year's end.

04:21.361 --> 04:24.631 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: The Fed's action
sent Wall Street
higher.

04:24.664 --> 04:30.971 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Dow Jones industrial average
gained 163
points to close at 18293.

04:31.004 --> 04:35.108 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Nasdaq rose nearly 54
points, and the
S&amp;P 500 added 23.

04:35.142 --> 04:40.847 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The crisis in
Syria took center
stage today at the U.N. Security
Council.

04:40.881 --> 04:46.186 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The U.S. and Russia clashed over
the failure
of the latest cease-fire, and
Monday's deadly

04:46.219 --> 04:48.455 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
attack on an aid convoy.

04:48.488 --> 04:54.327 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Russian Foreign Minister Sergei
Lavrov denied
responsibility and offered other
explanations.

04:54.361 --> 04:59.633 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But Secretary of State John
Kerry shot back,
"This is not a joke," and he
condemned what

04:59.666 --> 05:01.434 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
